{
  "stem": "20142.9",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And with me were the other members that we, that I mentioned from Skarzysko.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was Sam Bergman and Alek Ward, and Tsvi Karmi.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And at that time, his name was [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Andrew ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Weinberg. ?] And Chaim Yitskowic, Moishe Rosenblum, and all of us, we register.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And two days later, they packed us up on army trucks with plenty of food and all kinds of rations.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they made sure that we are well bathed and clean, with different clothing on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they brought us to the city of Regensburg to the American zone, because we wanted to migrate to other places and not to return to Poland, which we knew at that time was already under regime, Communist regime.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very close, we became sort of a family that did not need any blood relation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We still are writing and receiving in each other in a manner that perhaps some families could envy us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Of course, after the war, I did remember that I have a cousin in Israel who went to Israel in 1921 as a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [BACKROUND NOISE] he became one of the builders of Kibbutz [INAUDIBLE], and became a doctor of [INAUDIBLE], and also renowned for other achievement in the agricultural life.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His son remain in [INAUDIBLE], born in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm in constant contact with his two daughters and his son.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He passed away [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in October of '91--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--at the age of 87.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Israel Slomnicki, spelled S-L-O-M-N-I-C-K-I.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Quite a few times.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wanted and I wrote to him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And since I was looking for my brother, it just happened that my brother from Belgium I was writing-- wrote a letter to him, and I, as I wrote from Germany.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
